						<summary>

						<p>Registers a gift of gold by Malaikuṉiyaniṉṟaperumāḷ Ayyaṅgār, son of Vēdavyāsa Bhaṭṭar Iraṅgayyaṅgār of the Hārita-gōtra, for offerings to god on the occasion of his halt at the picture-hall (<hi rend="italic">Chittira-maṇḍapa</hi>) during the</p>						

						<p>1 Read �</p>						

						<p>2 The continuation is lost.</p>						

						<p>3 Read <hi rend="grantha">durmmukhi</hi>. <hi rend="bold">Kauśika (Kaisika) festival.</hi> The interest from the gold is to be utilised along with the interest accruing from a similar investment made in the year ṇandana. The date viś. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1459, ē1viḷambi</hi> (i.e. ḥēmaḷambi), Paṅguni may correspond to <hi rend="bold">1537 ā.ḍ., ṁarch.</hi></p>						

